        Official Singles Chart on 1/1/2021

        1 January 2021 - 7 January 2021

        The Official Singles Chart Top 100 reflects the UK’s biggest songs of the week, based on audio and video streams, downloads, CDs and vinyl, compiled by the Official Charts Company. The UK Top 40 is broadcast on BBC Radio 1. View the biggest songs of 2025.

        So, Wham has finally set a new chart record of taking 36 years to reach number one. Three years ago, and also (but not in the same year) Mariah set unwanted chart records by dropping from number two out of the 100 on the first chart of the New Year then when all the festive records dropped out.

        This week Ladbaby has a big drop from one to 78, not a record by any means but a significant fall to say the least.

        Correct me if I am wrong, but the current record holder of biggest drop from number one in a single week belongs to the Lightning Seeds with Three Lions when that tumbled down to 97 following England's defeat in the World Cup semi final during summer 2018.
        No single in chart history has ever fallen from one out of the hundred in a single week. This Friday that will change when Wham sets that most unwanted chart record.
        Also other chart records will be set, with the most number of dropouts out of the 100 in a single week as we kiss goodbye to all the festive records, a new record of re-entries will occur, the most number of singles in the top 10 to fall out of the 100 in a single week, with nine expected to go, you get the picture, I could go on but won't, so we all wait with baited breath for the new chart.

        I think the record is seven weeks for a #2 which has happened three times.
